Residents of six villages in Zamfara State who left their homes as a result of banditry returned  home  Thursday, Daily Trust learnt. Lilo, Fura Girke, Kowha, Kundumau,Yargeba and Bundugel villages were sacked by bandits and cattle rustlers at different times. They were returned through the office of the Senior Special Assistant  to the Governor on Security Matters, Alhaji Abubakar Muhammad Dauran. Some of them had spent over six months in Mada area of Gusau LGA but with the current measures said to have been put in place they were returned. Governor Matawalle through the Director General Press Affairs Alhaji Yusuf Idris commended the federal government for giving special consideration to Zamfara State through the deployment of more security personnel to the state that led to the return. The governor urged farmers in the state to go about their farming activities as according to him, all necessary measures have been put in place to ensure safety of lives and property.  Residents in six Zamfara villages return home Zamfara killings: Governor Yari in the eye of the storm Kidnappers: The rise of new criminal gangs in Zamfara Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin